Feature: TemporalParseAcceptance

  Scenario: Should parse date from string
    Given an empty graph
    When executing query:
      """
      UNWIND [date('2015-07-21'),
              date('20150721'),
              date('2015-07'),
              date('201507'),
              date('2015-W30-2'),
              date('2015W302'),
              date('2015-W30'),
              date('2015W30'),
              date('2015-202'),
              date('2015202'),
              date('2015')] as d
      RETURN d
      """
    Then the result should be, in order:
      | d            |
      | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015-07-01' |
      | '2015-07-01' |
      | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015-07-20' |
      | '2015-07-20' |
      | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015-01-01' |
    And no side effects

